data.enText: to take place at the same time

data.chText: 真遗憾我们不能同一时间去纽约旅行。
data.enText: It's a pity our trips to New York don't coincide.

data.chText: 那次罢工选择在召开政党大会的同一时间举行。
data.enText: The strike was timed to coincide with the party conference.
to be the same or very similar

data.chText: 雇主和雇员的利益并不总是一致的。
data.enText: The interests of employers and employees do not always coincide.

data.chText: 她和她兄弟所讲的完全一致。
data.enText: Her story coincided exactly with her brother's.

data.chText: 相接；相交；同位；位置重合；重叠
data.enText: to meet; to share the same space

data.chText: 两条小路在这个地方有一小段合在了一起。
data.enText: At this point the two paths coincide briefly.

data.chText: 这栋房子现在的位置恰与原住宅的位置一致。
data.enText: The present position of the house coincides with that of an earlier dwelling.

simple_means.memory_skill: co 共同 + in 使… + cid 落下；降临 + e → 使一同降临 → 巧合

ex.enText: This copy does not correspond with the original.

ex.chText: 这些标记与地图上的各点相对应。
ex.enText: The marks correspond to points on the map.

ex.chText: 他对事件的陈述与她说的不符。
ex.enText: His accounts of events do not correspond with hers.

synonyms.bx: 指两个事物或观点在某一方面或内容上互相匹配一致，常后接介词  with/to。

ex.chText: 她那漂亮的言辞与肮脏的行为不相符合。
ex.enText: Her beautiful words and dirty actions do not accord.

ex.chText: 你的行为与你的原则不符。
ex.enText: Your behaviour does not accord with your principle.

synonyms.bx: 常指行为、观点、性格、质量等方面一致，常后接介词 with。

ex.chText: 几个证人的陈述并不一致。
ex.enText: The witnesses' statements don't agree with each other.

ex.chText: 他的叙述和警方说的不一致。
ex.enText: His story doesn't agree with what the police have said.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指两条信息等相符或一致，常后接介词 with。

ex.chText: 我的宗教信仰跟你的不同。
ex.enText: My religious beliefs don't coincide with yours.

synonyms.bx: 多指想法、观点等一致或相符，常后接介词 with。

ex.chText: 我们对安排方面的意见与董事会一致。
ex.enText: Our opinions on the arrangement concur with those of the board.

ex.chText: 关于出口问题，我同意你的看法。
ex.enText: I concur with your opinion on exports.

synonyms.bx: 强调意见一致，一般用于正式场合，常后接介词 with。

ex.chText: 他的行为与社会习俗相左。
ex.enText: His behaviour doesn't conform to the customs of society.
Do you conform to the traffic rules?

synonyms.bx: 强调一致性，也指遵照已确立的规则或模式行事，常后接介词 to。

example: our views on this matter coincided

value.def: If one event coincides with another, they happen at the same time.

example.ex: The exhibition coincides with the 50th anniversary of his death...
example.tran: 展览恰好在他逝世50周年之际举行。

example.ex: Although his mental illness had coincided with his war service it had not been caused by it...
example.tran: 虽然他的精神病刚好在他参战期间发作，但并不是由此引起的。

example.ex: The beginning of the solar and lunar years coincided every 13 years.
example.tran: 太阳年和太阴年的起始时间每13年重合一次。

value.def: If the ideas or interests of two or more people coincide, they are the same.

example.ex: The kids' views on life don't always coincide, but they're not afraid of voicing their opinions...
example.tran: 孩子们的人生观并不总是一致，但他们敢于表达自己的观点。

example.ex: ...a case in which public and private interests coincide...
example.tran: 一个公众利益和私人利益一致的例子

example.ex: He gave great encouragement to his students, especially if their passions happened to coincide with his own.
example.tran: 他给予学生莫大的鼓励，尤其是当他们与自己志趣相投时。

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to fall, to drop, to fall down 落下；降临
rootsaffixes.title: cad, cas, cid, cay

partsOfSpeech.dec: cad 落下；降临 + ence 表行为 → 落下的〔声音〕→ 声音的抑扬
casc〔= cas〕落下；降临 + ade 表动作的结果 →〔水〕落下 → 小瀑布
cas 落下；降临 + ual 有…性质的 →〔没有准备〕降临的 → 偶然的
cas 落下；降临 + ual 有…性质的 + ty 表情况 →〔突然〕降临 → 事故
co 共同 + in 使… + cid 落下；降临 + e → 使一同降临 → 巧合
de 向下 + cad 落下；降临 + ent 具有…性质的，关于…的 → 向下堕落的 → 颓废的
de 向下 + cay 落下；降临 → 向下掉 → 衰退
de 加强 + cid 落下；降临 + uous …的 →〔树叶、表皮〕落下 → 落叶的；脱落的
in 使… + cid 落下；降临 + ent 表名词 → 使〔突然〕降临 → 偶然事件
oc 加强 + cas 落下；降临 + ion 表动作 → 使…降临 → 发生
oc 加强 + cid 落下；降临 + ent 表名词 →〔太阳〕落下的地方 → 西方
